Baoshan Steel May Buy More Parental Assets, Shanghai Daily Says

-- B y   J o s h u a   F e l l m a n
-- 
2011-03-31T20:00:23Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-03-31/baoshan-steel-may-buy-more-parental-assets-shanghai-daily-says.html
Baoshan Iron & Steel Co.’s parent
may inject assets including Xinjiang Ba Yi Iron & Steel Co. and
Ningbo Steel into the listed company "at the appropriate time,
Shanghai Daily says, citing Baoshan Chairman He Wenbo.  Baoshan Steel now accounts for about 60 percent of the
Baosteel Group Corp.’s capacity, and this may drop to 58 percent
next year as the parent expands, He said, as cited by the
English-language newspaper. Baosteel has no immediate plans to
list, he said.   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Joshua Fellman at 
 jfellman@bloomberg.net  